Access ranges slot in a SEMplScores object

Usage

getRanges(x)

# S4 method for class 'SEMplScores'
getRanges(x)

Arguments

x

a SEMplScores object

Value

A GRanges or VRanges object

# load default SEMs
data(SEMC)

# create a VRanges object
vr <- VRanges(
    seqnames = "chr12",
    ranges = 94136009,
    ref = "G", alt = "C"
)

# calculate binding propensity
s <- scoreVariants(vr, SEMC, BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19::Hsapiens)

getRanges(s)
#> VRanges object with 1 range and 3 metadata columns:
